A collision involving a cement truck was blocking all northbound lanes of Loop 101 in Scottsdale on Feb. 17, 2017. (Photo: ADOT) 
278 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE Two people were rushed to hospitals following an eight-vehicle collision involving a cement truck on northbound Loop 101 in Scottsdale on Friday morning.
Troopers with the Arizona Department of Public Safety arrived at the scene near McDonald Drive to find that the cement truck, which had tipped onto its side, spilled enough cement to stretch across two lanes of traffic.
As of about 9:30 a.m., the freeway closure was pushed back to Indian School Road.
The Arizona Department of Transportation said motorists can enter northbound Loop 101 at Indian Bend Road.
